<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="167" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kapustin, Glushchenko &amp; Kulikovskiy" authorityYear="2022" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Achnanthidium bratanense" order="Cocconeidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="bratanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Achnanthidium bratanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kulikovskiy, Glushchenko, Maltsev &amp; Kociolek" authorityYear="2020" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Gogorevia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Gogorevia rinatii" order="Cocconeidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="rinatii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Gogorevia rinatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were the most abundant species in the sample. Rarely single frustules of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F.E.Round &amp; L.Bukhtiyarova" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Planothidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Planothidium" order="Cocconeidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Planothidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.G.Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1843" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stauroneis" order="Naviculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Stauroneis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella" order="Cymbellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Cymbella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and other diatoms were encountered. During sampling the temperature was recorded as 25.7 °C, pH as 7.82, and conductivity as 22 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μS">μS</normalizedToken>
∙cm-1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
